ay all share the same origin near the GC at early stage\nof the bubble expansion. We find that the CR spatial and spectral distribution\npredicted by the leptonic jet model can simultaneously match the normalization,\nspectral shape, and high-energy cutoff of the observed gamma-ray spectrum and\ntheir spatial uniformity, suggesting that past AGN jet activity is a likely\nmechanism for the formation of the Fermi bubbles.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Jun 2017 18:12:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 30 Nov 2017 17:19:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-01"}
